\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8137580 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8347148\charrsid6645626 How many years did you live in the house where you were born?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16212999 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8347148\charrsid6645626 How many years? 'Til I was - twelve year old.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8137580 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8347148\charrsid6645626 You lived there for twelve years?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16212999 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8347148\charrsid6645626 Yes, then we came further down Fell Lane you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8137580 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8347148\charrsid6645626 So that house was at Fell Lane was it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16212999 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8347148\charrsid6645626 Mm.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8137580 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8347148\charrsid6645626 Where did you move to then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16212999 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8347148\charrsid6645626 Where did I move - we moved to - 34 Fell Lane, that's is it Knowle Park - Lund Park - is it Knowle Park at}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid11892120\charrsid6645626  bottom}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8347148\charrsid6645626  of Fell Lane?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8137580 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8347148\charrsid6645626 Yes, Lund Park.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16212999 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8347148\charrsid6645626 Number thirty-four there.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8137580 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8347148\charrsid6645626 How long did you stay there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16212999 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8347148\charrsid6645626 'Til - 19 - 19 - 1916, at Carby Grove. That's on the back of the - work house And - when I }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid11892120\charrsid6645626 were eighteen I had to go solde}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8347148\charrsid6645626 ring.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8137580 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8347148\charrsid6645626 So from 1916 to 1918 you were at Carby Grove?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16212999 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8347148\charrsid6645626 That's right.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8137580 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8347148\charrsid6645626 Do you remember why the family made these moves from one house to the other?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16212999 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8347148\charrsid6645626 Do remember what?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8137580 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8347148\charrsid6645626 Why your family made these moves?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16212999 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8347148\charrsid6645626 
Well - where - where we lived in Fell Lane it was two bedrooms and there were five children, and me mother and I - me mother and dad. And - sisters, they - they worked in a - in a Stell's Tube Mill, which got burnt down, and - at t
hat time - there were no glass to take the dust off where they were grinding tubes, and they got consumption. Yes, I had two died in one day, one eighteen and one twenty-one, one died from shock of the other, and two years after the other one died. Lost a
l
l three sisters. And - I don't remem - and than - the war started and you got called up on your birthday, eighteen you were, and - incidentally I weighed eighty-four pound - and I stood four foot height. Yes, and me pack were heavier than I was. And I wer
e that small that I had to go - into a regiment - the Royal Army Vet}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11892120\charrsid6645626 er}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8347148\charrsid6645626 
inary Corps - that was sick and wounded horses and all the - chaps that were there were all jockeys and stable boys, because we were small and it's only thing they could find us to do really. And - I were there throughout the war like, you know, to 1919.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8137580 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8347148\charrsid6645626 So in fact when you moved at first from the first house in Fell Lane to the second house in Fell Lane, was it to get a bigger house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16212999 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8347148\charrsid6645626 To get a bigger house.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8137580 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8347148\charrsid6645626 And when you moved - you moved from the first house in Fell Lane to the second house in Fell Lane to get a bigger house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16212999 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8347148\charrsid6645626 Mm.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8137580 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8347148\charrsid6645626 Why did you move from the second house in Fell Lane?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16212999 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8347148\charrsid6645626 To Carby Grove. Well - it was still a bigger house, we wanted more room, and 
- there's a big allotment, me father was very keen on rearing pigs and - a - apart from working you know, and - because in them days when they put the notice up - at works - these works will close down ten days, there were no pay nor nothing you know. My 
father always arranged that we had a pig to kill in that time, to help - us out and the neighbours as well you know - them that wanted it. Aye, they were hard times.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8137580 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8347148\charrsid6645626 How many brothers and sisters did you have? Could you tell me the names of your brothe
rs and sisters and how much difference there was in the ages?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16212999 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8347148\charrsid6645626 
In ages? Well - the youngest - the youngest was eighteen - the next was twenty-one, and the eldest was twenty-four. And - and they all died through this - this is - they call it thesis something in them days.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8137580 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8347148\charrsid6645626 Those were your sisters were they?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16212999 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8347148\charrsid6645626 Pardon?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8137580 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8347148\charrsid6645626 Those were your sister were they?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16212999 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8347148\charrsid6645626 They're my sisters, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8137580 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8347148\charrsid6645626 Did you have two brothers?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16212999 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8347148\charrsid6645626 And I had one brother.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8137580 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8347148\charrsid6645626 How much older was he?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16212999 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8347148\charrsid6645626 He - he were three years younger than me.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8137580 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8347148\charrsid6645626 Were you the eldest of the family?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16212999 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8347148\charrsid6645626 No, I - I - no, I wasn't - no, all the three sisters were older than me, see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8137580 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8347148\charrsid6645626 Was there about two years between each of them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16212999 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8347148\charrsid6645626 That's right.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8137580 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8347148\charrsid6645626 Then were you about two years younger?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16212999 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8347148\charrsid6645626 Mm.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8137580 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8347148\charrsid6645626 And then your brother was three years younger than you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16212999 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8347148\charrsid6645626 And the - yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8137580 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8347148\charrsid6645626 Do you know how old your father was when you were born?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16212999 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8347148\charrsid6645626 Me father? I think he was about - twenty-seven. When - when I was born? When I were b
orn. Oh he'd be thirty-three or something - be somewhere about their - you know, the difference in them ages you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8137580 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8347148\charrsid6645626 Could you tell me what his occupation was when you were born?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16212999 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8347148\charrsid6645626 My father's occupation? He was a steel forger. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8137580 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8347148\charrsid6645626 Did he have another job before or after he became that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16212999 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8347148\charrsid6645626 Did he have a job?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8137580 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8347148\charrsid6645626 Another job, other than being a steel forger? Either before he was or after
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16212999 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8347148\charrsid6645626 No - and do - do - during the war - during the war - they used to - well - well - they used to 
start at six o'clock and finish at six - and then he had to go - up to St Johns - where the - they have mental wards, and they used to take it - all do the night, after working, while six next morning, looking after these people. Gratis you know, they did
n't get anything for it. That's because they wanted - they - there }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9137040\charrsid6645626 wer}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8347148\charrsid6645626 
e more - they were more use doing their job than they would have been - soldiering you know, in the works. But they still had to fill their time in with 'em, so every other - every other night they'd to go as mill - nurses you see with the - mental wards.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8137580 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8347148\charrsid6645626 So he did that as a sort of part time non paid job did he?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16212999 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8347148\charrsid6645626 That's right.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8137580 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8347148\charrsid6645626 Did he do any jobs other than being a steel forger from the time he left school 'til the time he retired?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16212999 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8347148\charrsid6645626 No, he - he was on the same job.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8137580 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8347148\charrsid6645626 Constantly?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16212999 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8347148\charrsid6645626 Mm hn.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8137580 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8347148\charrsid6645626 This job that he did as a male nurse for nothing, was that the only part time job he had?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16212999 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8347148\charrsid6645626 That's right.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8137580 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8347148\charrsid6645626 He didn't do any other casual or part time jobs?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16212999 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8347148\charrsid6645626 No, he - of course - he reared pigs like in his spare time.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8137580 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8347148\charrsid6645626 Do you remember your father ever being out of work?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16212999 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8347148\charrsid6645626 Yes, when the - when there's a big strike on. Now would it be 19 - was it 1912? There's a general strike.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8137580 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8347148\charrsid6645626 It was an engineering strike was it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16212999 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8347148\charrsid6645626 Mm. Pardon? Engineering - no, it - yes, stell - what call a steelwork strike and it all closed down, and - it were horrible.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8137580 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8347148\charrsid6645626 How long was he out of work for, do you remember?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16212999 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8347148\charrsid6645626 Oh it went on about - it went on about twelve - twelve weeks this strike.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8137580 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8347148\charrsid6645626 At that time did you say he was working at Prince Smith's?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16212999 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8347148\charrsid6645626 Mm.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8137580 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8347148\charrsid6645626 Did the whole of Prince Smith's close at that time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16212999 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8347148\charrsid6645626 Did whole what?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8137580 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8347148\charrsid6645626 The whole of Prince Smith's works?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16212999 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8347148\charrsid6645626 Oh yes, the lot closed down, the lot closed down, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8137580 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8347148\charrsid6645626 Did the other engineering shops in Keighley close?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16212999 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8347148\charrsid6645626 
And there were nothing - there were nothing for 'em you know in them days I mean - just a - well they used to buy six savoury ducks and - spread 'em out and - had to make a meal of 'em you know. Anything that were going you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8137580 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8347148\charrsid6645626 Do you remember anything else about that time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16212999 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8347148\charrsid6645626 Pardon?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8137580 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8347148\charrsid6645626 Do you remember anything else about that time when your father was out of work?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16212999 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8347148\charrsid6645626 Well - nothing much, only the - we couldn't
 afford much gas you know and - didn't - well, I don't - coal, at that time it were about a penny a bucket you know down dump side and - and that's how - how you kept your fires going.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8137580 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8347148\charrsid6645626 Do you know how old your mother was when you were born?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16212999 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8347148\charrsid6645626 Mother was a year younger than me dad.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8137580 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8347148\charrsid6645626 How old was your mother when you were born, do you know?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16212999 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8347148\charrsid6645626 Oh - I think she'd be - thirty-seven - thirty-seven or thirty-eight.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8137580 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8347148\charrsid6645626 Do you know where she came from?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16212999 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8347148\charrsid6645626 She originally came from Bingley.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8137580 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8347148\charrsid6645626 Do you know where your father came from?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16212999 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8347148\charrsid6645626 
Yes, he were - he were born in Scotland. And - his father died and his mother got married again, and his stepfather, he were a cruel - he were cruel to him you know, and my father set off from - he left Scotlan
d, he - he lived in the Salt Market, East Side Glasgow - and he walked in his barefeet to Keighley.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8137580 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8347148\charrsid6645626 From Glasgow?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16212999 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8347148\charrsid6645626 And - he were stood at the gate of Prince Smith's - and the carriage and pair come round, the old - Prince Smith in it, and he nea
rly knocked him down, and he got out, he said, you want to clear off from here laddie, he says, you'll be get - if you'd have got knocked down then he said, you'd have been killed. What are you doing here anyway? He said, I'm looking for a job. Why, he sa
i
d, how old are you son? Thirteen. And - why have you run away from home and - he asked him all this, he says, well - and he took him to an old foreman in the shed, he said, now find this lad a job, and find him digs until he gets on his feet. And - that w
ere there start, and he worked there six - he worked there fifty-eight years me dad.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8137580 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8347148\charrsid6645626 So he originally came from Scotland?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16212999 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8347148\charrsid6645626 Mm. And they always call him Scottie. Then - then - and then - after that - I were young Scottie. And he used to say - there
's - there's Old Scottie and Young Scottie and Young Scottie's son, when old Scottie's gone, another begun.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8137580 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8347148\charrsid6645626 Your mother came from Bingley?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16212999 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8347148\charrsid6645626 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8137580 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8347148\charrsid6645626 Had she any jobs before she married?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16212999 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8347148\charrsid6645626 Oh she worked in a - in a spinning mill in Bingley. Mm.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8137580 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8347148\charrsid6645626 What did she do, was she a spinner?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16212999 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8347148\charrsid6645626 Yes, she was a spinner.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8137580 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8347148\charrsid6645626 Did she do this until she got married?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16212999 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8347148\charrsid6645626 'Til she got married.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8137580 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8347148\charrsid6645626 After she was married did she continue?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16212999 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8347148\charrsid6645626 No, because we had a little shop at Fell Lane. And - in the
 house where we - where we lived, that's why we moved you see because we had this little shop and - we hadn't - hadn't the accommodation you see, to get a bigger house.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8137580 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8347148\charrsid6645626 So after she was married she looked after this shop?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16212999 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8347148\charrsid6645626 That's right.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8137580 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8347148\charrsid6645626 How long did she do that for, did she do it for a long number of years?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16212999 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8347148\charrsid6645626 
She - she'd do it right - right from - the - the first - my - my oldest sister being born, until I was - eleven year old. Then we moved - down to Fell Lane you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8137580 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8347148\charrsid6645626 So she gave up the shop then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16212999 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8347148\charrsid6645626 That's right.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8137580 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8347148\charrsid6645626 Did she go out to work again then or not?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16212999 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8347148\charrsid6645626 No, no.. But she would - she used to take washings in.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8137580 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8347148\charrsid6645626 She did washing in at home?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16212999 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8347148\charrsid6645626 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8137580 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8347148\charrsid6645626 Did she ever do any other part time jobs or full time jobs from then on?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16212999 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8347148\charrsid6645626 
No, I reckon - no, because she had an accident in the yard and - and she died. Yes, she - got concussion or something, hanging clothes out or something and slipped and - and she died.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8137580 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8347148\charrsid6645626 When was that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16212999 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8347148\charrsid6645626 19 - 1916. Mm. Me father were left with all the family you see. Then he got married again.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8137580 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8347148\charrsid6645626 
I should like to ask you now about life at home when you were a child, the time up to when you left school, how many rooms were there in the house at Fell Lane?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16212999 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8347148\charrsid6645626 Two.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8137580 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8347148\charrsid6645626 There were two downstairs?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16212999 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8347148\charrsid6645626 No - two - there were two bedrooms, and - the living room - was a shop. And there's of course a back kitchen.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8137580 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8347148\charrsid6645626 So you just had three rooms for living?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16212999 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8347148\charrsid6645626 That's right.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8137580 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8347148\charrsid6645626 Two bedrooms and one room?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16212999 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8347148\charrsid6645626 Mm.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8137580 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8347148\charrsid6645626 Where you cooked and ate?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16212999 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8347148\charrsid6645626 That's right. The seven of us. Counting mother and father.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8137580 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8347148\charrsid6645626 Did anyone else besides your parents and brothers and sisters live in the house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16212999 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8347148\charrsid6645626 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8137580 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8347148\charrsid6645626 No other relatives or lodgers. Did your mother pay anyone to help in the house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16212999 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8347148\charrsid6645626 She couldn't afford it. mm. Mm. That's right.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8137580 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8347148\charrsid6645626 You said she did other peoples' washing, was the washing done at home or sent out?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16212999 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8347148\charrsid6645626 No, it were done at home. The old wringing machine.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8137580 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8347148\charrsid6645626 Did your mother or father mend or make the family's clothes?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16212999 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8347148\charrsid6645626 Mother was sewer, she used to make - make for the girls you know but - she kept us decent you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8137580 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8347148\charrsid6645626 Were the clothes new or second}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9137040\charrsid6645626  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid8347148\charrsid6645626 hand?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16212999 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8347148\charrsid6645626 Oh they wasn't always new. No. I - we - we had a lot of hand me downs you know. From richer relations.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8137580 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8347148\charrsid6645626 So you and your brother had this as well?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16212999 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8347148\charrsid6645626 That's right, yes, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8137580 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8347148\charrsid6645626 Did you ever get new clothes at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16212999 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8347148\charrsid6645626 Well - we got one - one - one Sunday suit. And - and - and a pair of shoes, but - all - any other time we wore clogs
, everybody wore clogs.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8137580 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8347148\charrsid6645626 When you got new clothes where were they bought, do you remember?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16212999 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8347148\charrsid6645626 Chadwick}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9137040\charrsid6645626 \rquote }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid8347148\charrsid6645626 s.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8137580 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8347148\charrsid6645626 Where's that, in Keighley?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16212999 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8347148\charrsid6645626 Well - it used to be a - it - Ram - you know where Ramsbottom's is now? That were Chadwick}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid9137040\charrsid6645626 \rquote }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8347148\charrsid6645626 s. And - you could always get cheap clothes there. And incidentally it were a - next - it was pawn shop as well.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8137580 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8347148\charrsid6645626 So it was a pawnshop and men}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9137040\charrsid6645626 \rquote }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid8347148\charrsid6645626 s outfitters as well?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16212999 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8347148\charrsid6645626 That's right.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8137580 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8347148\charrsid6645626 You and your brother got your clothes there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16212999 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8347148\charrsid6645626 Mm.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8137580 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8347148\charrsid6645626 When did you get new clothes? Was there a certain time of year when you bought them or was it only every few years?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16212999 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8347148\charrsid6645626 Well - we - we - we used - we used to get a new suit - in twelve months. Mm.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8137580 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8347148\charrsid6645626 Do you remember when you used to get it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16212999 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8347148\charrsid6645626 Well it were - it were always about Easter time. Mm.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8137580 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8347148\charrsid6645626 Did the girls have new dresses?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16212999 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8347148\charrsid6645626 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8137580 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8347148\charrsid6645626 Did your mother or father ever make or mend shoes?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16212999 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8347148\charrsid6645626 Me - me father used to clog. He - he - what were called clog - he used to iron us clogs you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8137580 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8347148\charrsid6645626 Did he repair your shoes as well?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16212999 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8347148\charrsid6645626 We - we all had a pair of shoes for Sunday.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8137580 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8347148\charrsid6645626 Would he repair them when they were getting a bit worn?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16212999 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8347148\charrsid6645626 That's right.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8137580 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8347148\charrsid6645626 Were your shoes new or second}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9137040\charrsid6645626  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid8347148\charrsid6645626 hand?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16212999 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8347148\charrsid6645626 Well - I always got a pair of - I - no, I'd get a pair
 of new shoes, and - they were never thrown away because they always came in for me brother after. Hand me downs.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8137580 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8347148\charrsid6645626 So you would have new shoes?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16212999 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8347148\charrsid6645626 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8137580 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8347148\charrsid6645626 And your brother would have second}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9137040\charrsid6645626  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid8347148\charrsid6645626 hand shoes?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16212999 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8347148\charrsid6645626 Mm. That's right.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8137580 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8347148\charrsid6645626 Do you remember where you used to get your shoes?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16212999 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8347148\charrsid6645626 
Now then, I for - it were in the market, Keithley market place, and they used to have - Saturday afternoon sales you know, and - and go round and try and baton 'em down you know, get 'em a bit cheaper and all that, mm.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8137580 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8347148\charrsid6645626 So it was in Keighley market you used to get shoes?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16212999 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8347148\charrsid6645626 Mm.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8137580 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8347148\charrsid6645626 Where did you get your clogs?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16212999 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8347148\charrsid6645626 Where did you get what?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8137580 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8347148\charrsid6645626 Your clogs?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16212999 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8347148\charrsid6645626 Clogs always from the Co-op.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8137580 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8347148\charrsid6645626 You always wore clogs for school did you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16212999 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8347148\charrsid6645626 That's right.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8137580 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8347148\charrsid6645626 How often would you get new shoes, would you get those every year or every two years or how often?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16212999 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8347148\charrsid6645626 You - you - you got 'em when the others were ready for dropping off your feet.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8137580 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8347148\charrsid6645626 Just when they were absolutely necessary?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16212999 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8347148\charrsid6645626 That's right. Mm. But they lasted a long while because you only got to wear them at Sunday you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8137580 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8347148\charrsid6645626 So presumably you had to get them plenty big enough so they would last?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16212999 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8347148\charrsid6645626 That's right.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8137580 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8347148\charrsid6645626 Did your father help - your mother with any of the jobs in the house? Such as cleaning, cooking, washing up?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16212999 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8347148\charrsid6645626 
No, father were always busy - because at that time when we had this little shop at Fell Lane, he had the donkey and cart. And I used to - meet him on Saturday dinnertimes at twelve o'clock, with the cart, I used to work in the High Street, and he'd co}{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9137040\charrsid6645626 me and get all the stuff at Towns}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8347148\charrsid6645626 end}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9137040\charrsid6645626 \rquote }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8347148\charrsid6645626 s - at end of Temple Street and - check it over you know, and - he - it went on for years and - there were these strikes on and people getting on the tick and all that you know
 - me father used to say, you make enemies with - with lending stuff - with - with lending you know, see and when - when the strike had finished they'd walk past and wouldn't let on to him you know, and he said he'd three books, he said, if everybody paid
 me what they owe me I could have retired, you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8137580 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8347148\charrsid6645626 So he had this donkey and cart and what did you do, what did you get on the donkey and cart?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16212999 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8347148\charrsid6645626 We-l I used to fetch bottles - boxes of pop up you know from - from the town and - the flour and all
 that, from - from the provision merchants and they used to sell it out retail you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8137580 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8347148\charrsid6645626 Was this for you to resell? Or was this for your own use?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16212999 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8347148\charrsid6645626 No, no for retail you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8137580 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8347148\charrsid6645626 For you to sell at the shop?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16212999 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8347148\charrsid6645626 Yes. And - and we had - we - we lived out of it as well you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8137580 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8347148\charrsid6645626 It was a sort of cash and carry sort of place?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16212999 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8347148\charrsid6645626 Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8137580 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8347148\charrsid6645626 And you used to bring it all up to the shop?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16212999 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8347148\charrsid6645626 That's right.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8137580 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8347148\charrsid6645626 And then sell it there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16212999 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8347148\charrsid6645626 Mm.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8137580 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8347148\charrsid6645626 So you said he didn't have much time to help cleaning and cooking? Did he ever do any washing up for your mother?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16212999 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8347148\charrsid6645626 No, I don't think he did because with all those - sisters that had - we all had us own jobs in the house you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8137580 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8347148\charrsid6645626 Did he make the fires in the morning?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16212999 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8347148\charrsid6645626 Pardon?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8137580 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8347148\charrsid6645626 Did he make the fires in the morning?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16212999 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8347148\charrsid6645626 Oh yes, they always did that, yes, oh before he went to work.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8137580 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8347148\charrsid6645626 Do you remember him ever doing any decorating or repairs or improvements to the house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16212999 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8347148\charrsid6645626 Oh he - well they did a lot of whitewashing in them days.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8137580 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8347148\charrsid6645626 Did he do repairs?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16212999 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8347148\charrsid6645626 Oh yes, he did a lot of repairs.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8137580 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8347148\charrsid6645626 Did he ever do any improvements to the house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16212999 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8347148\charrsid6645626 Well he used to put - he used to put slates on when they came off. And if - if the chimney wanted sweeping they used to drop a 
lath end down it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8137580 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8347148\charrsid6645626 
When you were very small do you remember him ever helping your mother by dressing the small children or undressing them, or bathing you, or reading to you, anything like that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16212999 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8347148\charrsid6645626 Mother?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8137580 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8347148\charrsid6645626 Did your father ever do these things, to help your mother out?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16212999 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8347148\charrsid6645626 No, father was always - always busy outside with his - with his poult}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9137040\charrsid6645626 r}{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8347148\charrsid6645626 y and pigs and his work and - he didn't do a right lot at home but because - the family were brought up to all do their own jobs. You know - you all - helped - helped one - did your own jobs.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8137580 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8347148\charrsid6645626 Do you remember him ever reading to you or telling you stories?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16212999 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8347148\charrsid6645626 
Oh yes, mother used to read - she - she - every night she used to read a passage out of the Bible to us all around - on our knees and we all said us prayers and - off to bed. We - we were Wesleyans and brought up.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8137580 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8347148\charrsid6645626 Did your father ever read to you?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16212999 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8347148\charrsid6645626 Well no, not much, no. No, mother used to do most of it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8137580 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8347148\charrsid6645626 Do you remember him ever taking you out without your mother?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16212999 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8347148\charrsid6645626 Oh yes. He 
used to say - right, we'll go to Morecambe. And in them days you could go to Morecambe for half a day for half a crown, adults. And kiddies a shilling. And there were five of us and we used to - get on the train - of course mother had to stay at home to l
o
ok after the shop. And he'd take us to Morecambe, the end - you know the old clock on the front, he'd put us all there, we used to take always apples and - whatever we had you know, and play there all day and me father used to go and have a - drink I supp
ose, and - we used to get back - back at Keighley and going up Fell Lane at twelve o'clock at night. One - one on his shoulders and one on his back and the rest having to trot at side.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8137580 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8347148\charrsid6645626 He did it quite often did he?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16212999 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8347148\charrsid6645626 Oh yes. Every time there were - every time there were these trips on he used to -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8137580 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8347148\charrsid6645626 Did he ever look after you when she was out?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16212999 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8347148\charrsid6645626 She - mother very very rarely went out. She - she - she were really tied to the house you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8137580 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8347148\charrsid6645626 So you don't remember him ever looking after you while she went out?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16212999 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8347148\charrsid6645626 No, no. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8137580 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8347148\charrsid6645626 Did you have any tasks you had to carry out regularly at home to help?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16212999 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8347148\charrsid6645626 Yes, I'd - I used to have to - I used to have to groom the donkey. And muck the pigs out. And gather the eggs. All sorts of little jobs
, chop all the wood you know and - it were always my job to fetch the coal in. But - as - and - but as - and as you got older you got different tasks you see. The younger one followed on what I used to do. And - and I - and I - me father always found me a
 job where I could go - go - go and earn a bit of money you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8137580 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8347148\charrsid6645626 How long did you continue doing these tasks?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16212999 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8347148\charrsid6645626 Well, I did - I - when I started on this paper round - the jobs that I used to have to do - me brother had to do. And I used to leave ho
me at six o'clock in the morning and used to leave here and - and then go on the paper round, I got one and nine a week for that. And that was six days a week. And as for - and had to ask for something - extra, tuppence, they wouldn't give me it. So me fa
t
her said finish. He said, that's going in mill next week and - I started in the mill at twelve year old. Now - when you started you got half a crown a week while you were learning for a fortnight. And then - then it got to - it - it got to four and six. B
ut you'd to work at morning - go to school in the afternoon and the next week - you - you started at dinnertime and worked 'til night. And that went on and on until you were full time, thirteen year old.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8137580 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8347148\charrsid6645626 Once you'd started working you stopped doing all the jobs in the house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16212999 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8347148\charrsid6645626 
You had - you - you - you hadn't time for any more jobs you know. No. There were no buses, there was no tax - nothing you know, it were - you'd to walk every inch of the way you know wherever you went.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8137580 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8347148\charrsid6645626 You told me that your brother, once you stopped doing these jobs, he took over where you'd left off?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16212999 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8347148\charrsid6645626 That's right.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8137580 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8347148\charrsid6645626 Do you remember what the sisters used to do about the house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16212999 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8347148\charrsid6645626 One used to do the ironing - another did the cleaning, another did the - and it were all brass}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid9137040\charrsid6645626 -}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8347148\charrsid6645626 
work round the fireplace you know, and - and there's a special mending night every Thursday night, everybody - all the girls had to mend their own stuff. And - they - they were kept fully occupied you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8137580 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8347148\charrsid6645626 Did the older children help the younger with things they found difficult, such as dressing or eating?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16212999 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8347148\charrsid6645626 
Yes, you all had to help one another. The - the - the eld - the eldest - helped - the next and - and it went down and down 'til you were all ready. And all ready for off for school and that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8137580 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8347148\charrsid6645626 In dressing in the morning you used to help each other?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16212999 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8347148\charrsid6645626 Mm. Yes. You all had to help one another.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8137580 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8347148\charrsid6645626 Do you remember helping the little brother to eat, or perhaps one of the sisters helping the little brother to eat?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16212999 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8347148\charrsid6645626 To eat? Oh yes, yes - yes, they - you all had to rear one another in them days.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8137580 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8347148\charrsid6645626 Do you remember ever the younger children help in the older ones in any way?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16212999 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8347148\charrsid6645626 No, we seem}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9137040\charrsid6645626 e}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8347148\charrsid6645626 
d to get under feet a lot.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8137580 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8347148\charrsid6645626 Were you expected to go to bed at a certain time in your schooldays?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16212999 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8347148\charrsid6645626 
Yes. In - if - in - in winter - we were all in bed by six o'clock, all - all the kiddies. And in summer, well, it were nine, they had to chase us in you know. And in them days when it was summer we never had shoe - never had boots 
or socks on you know, we were always in your bare}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9137040\charrsid6645626  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8347148\charrsid6645626 
feet and playing round Old Marsh Wood and - but we had to be home at a certain time. But at Sun - we had to go to school at Sunday, every - everybody went to Sunday school. And if you weren't in at twelve o
'clock - you didn't get your dinner. Do without. And you didn't do that often.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8137580 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8347148\charrsid6645626 Did your mother or anyone else put you to bed?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16212999 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8347148\charrsid6645626 Mother always - no, mother always saw us to bed. Eldest went - the youngest went first and they followed on and up in - in steps.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8137580 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8347148\charrsid6645626 Do you remember what age you were when you put yourself to bed?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16212999 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8347148\charrsid6645626 Oh - six year old.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8137580 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8347148\charrsid6645626 Did you share the bedroom or bed with anyone?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16212999 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8347148\charrsid6645626 Yes, I shared it with - one sister and - and me brother.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8137580 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8347148\charrsid6645626 That was one bed or one bedroom?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16212999 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8347148\charrsid6645626 Mm. Yes. And two - and the other two sisters - in another bed, and the mother and father in a little - bedroom of their own at the back.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8137580 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8347148\charrsid6645626 So all five of you were in the one bedroom?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16212999 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8347148\charrsid6645626 That's right.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8137580 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8347148\charrsid6645626 And three in one bed?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16212999 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8347148\charrsid6645626 Mm.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8137580 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8347148\charrsid6645626 And two in another bed?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16212999 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8347148\charrsid6645626 That's right.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8137580 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8347148\charrsid6645626 And your parents in a double bed in the other bedroom?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16212999 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8347148\charrsid6645626 That's right.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8137580 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8347148\charrsid6645626 What room did you bath in?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16212999 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8347148\charrsid6645626 In - in the kitchen. A tin bath. Hung on a nail on the wall outside.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8137580 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8347148\charrsid6645626 How often did you have a bath, do you remember?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16212999 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8347148\charrsid6645626 Three times a week. Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8137580 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8347148\charrsid6645626 How often did you have clean clothes?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16212999 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8347148\charrsid6645626 How often what?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8137580 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8347148\charrsid6645626 Did you have clean clothes to put on?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16212999 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8347148\charrsid6645626 Oh - we'd - we'd a - a change - of a shirt - twice a week, but the bests one were always kept for Sunday.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8137580 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8347148\charrsid6645626 How often did you change underwear?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16212999 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8347148\charrsid6645626 Once a week.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8137580 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8347148\charrsid6645626 You've already told me that the family had their meals in the living room kitchen?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16212999 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8347148\charrsid6645626 That's right.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8137580 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8347148\charrsid6645626 Were there any occasions when they ate in another room, you didn't have another room where you could eat in did you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16212999 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8347148\charrsid6645626 No. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8137580 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8347148\charrsid6645626 You would never eat in a bedroom?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16212999 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8347148\charrsid6645626 No, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8137580 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8347148\charrsid6645626 Where did your mother cook? She must have cooked in the same room?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16212999 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8347148\charrsid6645626 It - it - it - it was a - it was what's called a cellar end you know. That's right.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8137580 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8347148\charrsid6645626 There was a little sort of scullery at the top of the cellar steps?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16212999 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8347148\charrsid6645626 That's right. That's right. Mm. That's right.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8137580 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8347148\charrsid6645626 What was her cooking equipment?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16212999 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8347148\charrsid6645626 Well just a gas oven in them days but there was alwa
ys a - a - they had a - oven you know, in the house, mm. Where they used to do the baking and all that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8137580 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8347148\charrsid6645626 Is that what you'd call a range?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16212999 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8347148\charrsid6645626 That's right. That's right, range.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8137580 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8347148\charrsid6645626 What did you refer to the various meals during the day, you had breakfast? What did you call your midday meal?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16212999 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8347148\charrsid6645626 Dinner. Always dinner.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8137580 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8347148\charrsid6645626 And did you call it tea?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16212999 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8347148\charrsid6645626 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8137580 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8347148\charrsid6645626 Could you tell me when breakfast was eaten, what time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16212999 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8347148\charrsid6645626 Well - in - in them days when the - when the girls were working they had to b
e before six o'clock you see, they had to leave at here at six o'clock, before six, and then they got their breakfast at work.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8137580 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8347148\charrsid6645626 And how about you at school, when you were at school what time did you have your breakfast?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16212999 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8347148\charrsid6645626 Well, I used to get mine w
hen me father you see, in the morning because I were doing this paper round, and I'd to wait until dinnertime before I got anything else.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8137580 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8347148\charrsid6645626 Before you started your paper round, presumably there was just you and your younger brother and mother, what time
 would you have your breakfast then, do you remember?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16212999 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8347148\charrsid6645626 Always eight o'clock in the morning.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8137580 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8347148\charrsid6645626 
All those others who were working, such as your father and elder sisters, how did they manage for their breakfast, what did they do for breakfast?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16212999 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8347148\charrsid6645626 Pardon?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8137580 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8347148\charrsid6645626 How did your father and elder sisters go on for their breakfast, those who were at work? Did they have it before they went?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16212999 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8347148\charrsid6645626 They had it - no, they used to have their breakfast at work. Mm.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8137580 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8347148\charrsid6645626 Did they take it with them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16212999 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8347148\charrsid6645626 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8137580 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8347148\charrsid6645626 They took something with them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16212999 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8347148\charrsid6645626 That's right. And the old tea can to warm up you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8137580 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8347148\charrsid6645626 What did you usually have to eat and drink at breakfast time, do you remember?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16212999 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8347148\charrsid6645626 Well - I can remember bread and dripping more than anything else.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8137580 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8347148\charrsid6645626 Did you have anything different on certain days, such as Sunday?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16212999 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8347148\charrsid6645626 
Oh yes, we always had the Yorkshire pudding on Sunday and - with meat and potatoes and - weren't as good some weeks as others when times were bad you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8137580 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8347148\charrsid6645626 That was at dinnertime wasn't it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16212999 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8347148\charrsid6645626 mm.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8137580 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8347148\charrsid6645626 But at breakfast time do you remember having anything special on a Sunday?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16212999 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8347148\charrsid6645626 We - well - the - father - father and mother used to have bacon and egg and - we used to get a dip off it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8137580 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8347148\charrsid6645626 You never had eggs yourself for breakfast. Do you remember what time you had dinner?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16212999 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8347148\charrsid6645626 
Well it - when were at school it - it - it were - it would just take us half an hour to get home you know from school. It'd be half past twelve. And - you'd have to leave just after one to get back to scho
ol. You know it's a long from top of Fell Lane down to - Holycroft you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8137580 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8347148\charrsid6645626 
How did the others manage for their dinner, those who were at work, such as your father? Could you remember who was there to have dinner with you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16212999 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8347148\charrsid6645626 Could I remember what?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8137580 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8347148\charrsid6645626 Who would have dinner with you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16212999 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8347148\charrsid6645626 There - there's only - there's only - only mother and the - and the sisters and - father never came home to his dinner.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8137580 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8347148\charrsid6645626 There were just the children?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16212999 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8347148\charrsid6645626 Mm.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8137580 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8347148\charrsid6645626 How did your father manage for his dinner?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16212999 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8347148\charrsid6645626 Father used to take it. Mm. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8137580 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8347148\charrsid6645626 For your dinner what did you usually have to eat and drink?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16212999 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8347148\charrsid6645626 
Well - it was always tea for drinking, and - when - father always used to be able to buy a big hambone at the weekend - and - that helped out w
ith - with the dinners a lot. Very rarely did we get - fresh meat. Butchers meat you know. We got - always got it At Saturday and Sunday but after that - we got what - we could cop you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8137580 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8347148\charrsid6645626 What would that be do you think?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16212999 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8347148\charrsid6645626 Well I've known mother - she used to buy six savoury ducks and - and put potatoes and make a meal of it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8137580 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8347148\charrsid6645626 Can you remember anything else that you used to have?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16212999 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8347148\charrsid6645626 Well - we seemed to be, it were all rice puddings in them days and Yorkshire puddings you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8137580 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8347148\charrsid6645626 Did yo
u have anything different on certain days, on Sunday perhaps? You already told me that on a Sunday dinnertime you'd have roast beef and Yorkshire pudding?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16212999 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8347148\charrsid6645626 We all - we always had that - a good Sunday dinner.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8137580 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8347148\charrsid6645626 So on a Sunday dinnertime you'd have roast beef and Yorkshire pudding?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16212999 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8347148\charrsid6645626 That's right.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8137580 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8347148\charrsid6645626 Did you have anything different on a Saturday?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16212999 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8347148\charrsid6645626 No, nothing special on Saturdays.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8137580 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8347148\charrsid6645626 Did you used to have a pudding to finish off with?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16212999 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8347148\charrsid6645626 We always had rice. Rice pudding.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8137580 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8347148\charrsid6645626 For teatime, what time would you have tea when you were at school?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16212999 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8347148\charrsid6645626 Well - at - everybody at five o'clock.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8137580 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8347148\charrsid6645626 What members of the family were present then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16212999 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8347148\charrsid6645626 There were the - three sisters, the brother and I.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8137580 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8347148\charrsid6645626 What about your father?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16212999 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8347148\charrsid6645626 And father used to have his when he came home because - he didn't get home while six o'clock you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8137580 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8347148\charrsid6645626 Do you remember what you used to have for tea?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16212999 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8347148\charrsid6645626 Well - cheese - was a - the main thing, seem to have been brought up on cheese in them days.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8137580 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8347148\charrsid6645626 Just cheese would it be?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16212999 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8347148\charrsid6645626 
Mm. And - if there was any fat, bacon fat left, dripping you know - two or three slices of dripping. And happen a home made - cake that mother had made for us. Mm.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8137580 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8347148\charrsid6645626 Did you have anything different on certain days such as Sundays for tea?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16212999 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8347148\charrsid6645626 Did what?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8137580 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8347148\charrsid6645626 Did you have anything different on Sunday for tea?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16212999 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8347148\charrsid6645626 We always had, yes, we'd always a - custard and jelly or some - some - tinned fruit or something like that. Mm. Mm.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8137580 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8347148\charrsid6645626 Did your mother or father bake their own bread?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16212999 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8347148\charrsid6645626 She always baked her own bread.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8137580 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8347148\charrsid6645626 Did she make her own jam?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16212999 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8347148\charrsid6645626 No, no, no, she didn't.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8137580 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8347148\charrsid6645626 Do you remember her ever bottling fruit or vegetables?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16212999 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8347148\charrsid6645626 No, because - we - we - with her having this little shop - and we used to have a lot of the
 stuff that we sold - we sold retail you see that - we lived off the shop as well you see.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8137580 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8347148\charrsid6645626 Do you remember her ever making pickles, or wine, or medicines?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16212999 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8347148\charrsid6645626 No. The only time we got medicines is when we'd - a bad cough or anything like that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8137580 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8347148\charrsid6645626 Did she make it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16212999 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8347148\charrsid6645626 No, no, she - she used to buy it at the chemist, it were only about threepence a bottle then.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8137580 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8347148\charrsid6645626 Do you remember her ever brewing beer for the family?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16212999 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8347148\charrsid6645626 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8137580 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8347148\charrsid6645626 Did your father or mother grow their own vegetables and fruit?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16212999 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8347148\charrsid6645626 Did they what?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8137580 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8347148\charrsid6645626 Grow their own vegetables?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16212999 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8347148\charrsid6645626 No, no, there wasn't room to grow anything like that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8137580 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8347148\charrsid6645626 Did they buy vegetables and fruit?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16212999 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8347148\charrsid6645626 Oh yes, they - they bought - they bought apples and - oranges and - of course they were very cheap
. But that had to last you all week that you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8137580 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8347148\charrsid6645626 Did they ever buy any vegetables, cabbages, peas, carrots?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16212999 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8347148\charrsid6645626 Oh - he - he - he used to - he used to - call in the market, and when it were getting near closing time, and buy whatever they could ch
eap you know. A rabbit at sixpence. And in them days there used to be a fellow that you could get a rabbit, half a stone of potatoes, onions and - and carrots - the lot for a shilling. And that did for the family.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8137580 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8347148\charrsid6645626 Do you ever remember having tinned or
 dried vegetables or fruit? You've already told me that you used to have tinned fruit at Sunday teatime.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16212999 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8347148\charrsid6645626 Mm.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8137580 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8347148\charrsid6645626 Do you ever remember having any tinned vegetables?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16212999 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8347148\charrsid6645626 No, never.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8137580 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8347148\charrsid6645626 You've already told me that you kept pigs.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16212999 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8347148\charrsid6645626 Mm.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8137580 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8347148\charrsid6645626 You kept hens as well did you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16212999 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8347148\charrsid6645626 Yes, we kept - kept a few hens and -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8137580 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8347148\charrsid6645626 Anything else?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16212999 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8347148\charrsid6645626 No. We had a goat at one time, when we - we - we lived off the goat milk.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8137580 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8347148\charrsid6645626 He kept all these in an allotment did he?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16212999 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8347148\charrsid6645626 Well all at back of the house, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8137580 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8347148\charrsid6645626 Was it just one pig?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16212999 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8347148\charrsid6645626 
He always - he always had - one sow on and a few - and a litter of young ones. Kept - he always kept one - one for home and the rest to sell - to - implement his wages you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8137580 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8347148\charrsid6645626 You've already told me that you helped him look after them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16212999 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8347148\charrsid6645626 Mm.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8137580 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8347148\charrsid6645626 You used to clean them out and things, did your father look after them as well?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16212999 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8347148\charrsid6645626 Did he what?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8137580 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8347148\charrsid6645626 Did he look after the livestock as well?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16212999 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8347148\charrsid6645626 Oh yes, yes, father - his first job in the morning were to feed up - feed all round you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8137580 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8347148\charrsid6645626 And you used to just help cleaning out and things like that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16212999 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8347148\charrsid6645626 That's right.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8137580 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8347148\charrsid6645626 Do you remember how many times a week you would eat meat?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16212999 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8347148\charrsid6645626 I reckon - meat - twice a week.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8137580 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8347148\charrsid6645626 That was fresh meat from the butchers?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16212999 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8347148\charrsid6645626 That's right.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8137580 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8347148\charrsid6645626 Did you have any other sort of meat other than that, perhaps tinned meat?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16212999 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8347148\charrsid6645626 No, we didn't have any tinned meat, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8137580 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8347148\charrsid6645626 Did you ever have potted meat?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16212999 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8347148\charrsid6645626 Oh we - yes, we used to have potted meat at tuppence a quarter. Mm.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8137580 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8347148\charrsid6645626 And you had that perhaps once a week did you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16212999 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8347148\charrsid6645626 Mm.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8137580 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8347148\charrsid6645626 You said you had savoury ducks?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16212999 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8347148\charrsid6645626 Savoury -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8137580 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8347148\charrsid6645626 They're made of meat aren't they?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16212999 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8347148\charrsid6645626 They - they - they're - they're a mixture of meat - and - cereals and all sorts of things in 'em.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8137580 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8347148\charrsid6645626 How about sausages, did you have those?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16212999 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8347148\charrsid6645626 We - we used to get sausages about once a week.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8137580 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8347148\charrsid6645626 So altogether you had meat in various forms perhaps five or six times a week?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16212999 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8347148\charrsid6645626 That's right. Mm. But if father hadn't have been a tower - and - w
orking and doing - other jobs you know, wherever he went he always picked a - a bit of something you know. He always kept the home going, he always looked after us for - as where our stomachs were concerned you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8137580 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8347148\charrsid6645626 What do you mean by picking something up, do you mean he got things cheap?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16212999 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8347148\charrsid6645626 Yes, he used to - he used to get - what had they going cheap and - used to go - yes, mm.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8137580 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8347148\charrsid6645626 Did you ever get some extra meat such as a rabbit from poaching? Did you know anyone who did any poaching?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16212999 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8347148\charrsid6645626 No. In - in those days rabbits you could buy for sixpence each you know. And become a - staple diet. Mm.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8137580 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8347148\charrsid6645626 Do you remember ever seeing your mother having less food so that the family could have more?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16212999 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8347148\charrsid6645626 In many a time. She - many a time she said she w
ere - she wasn't hungry. And we realized many a time that - she could have done with it you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8137580 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8347148\charrsid6645626 Were you allowed to talk during meals or not?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16212999 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8347148\charrsid6645626 No. No. You weren't - me father used to say, you can't eat and talk. If you're going to talk you're not going to eat. And that were it.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8137580 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8347148\charrsid6645626 Could you choose what you wanted to eat from what was cooked or did you have to eat a bit of everything?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16212999 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8347148\charrsid6645626 You had to eat - what were there, and you were glad of it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8137580 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8347148\charrsid6645626 What was your parents attitude if you left some food uneaten on your plate?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16212999 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8347148\charrsid6645626 He'd say - well - you won't want any tea if you don't want your dinner.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8137580 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8347148\charrsid6645626 So usually you ate it up did you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16212999 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8347148\charrsid6645626 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8137580 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8347148\charrsid6645626 If there was something on the table you wanted like the salt, could you ask someone to p
ass it to you, or did you have to wait until it was offered to you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16212999 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8347148\charrsid6645626 No, you'd to ask for it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8137580 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8347148\charrsid6645626 Could you ask for a second helping?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16212999 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8347148\charrsid6645626 You could ask but you wasn't forced to get it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8137580 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8347148\charrsid6645626 Were you expected to hold your knife and fork in a certain way and sit in a certain way?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16212999 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8347148\charrsid6645626 
We - well - were - were learnt how to use knives and forks. We learnt table manners as well. And we never had - we - and - Sunday - they always the grace said by father. Yes, and - no one started - anything - all eyes d
own. Yes. And it were the old - it were the old saying you know, we thank the Lord for this food, most of all through Jesus blood, manna to our soul be given this bitter life sent down from heaven, then you could start in, but they were very strict on hym
ns.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8137580 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8347148\charrsid6645626 Could you bring toys or a book to the table?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16212999 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8347148\charrsid6645626 Could I what luv?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8137580 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8347148\charrsid6645626 Could you bring toys or a book to the table?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16212999 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8347148\charrsid6645626 No, no, nothing at all, no. Weren't allowed to read.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8137580 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8347148\charrsid6645626 When could you leave the table?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16212999 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8347148\charrsid6645626 When - when they'd all finished, there were no getting up - you all had to - wait 'til they'd all finished.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8137580 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8347148\charrsid6645626 Did all the family sit at the table for the meal?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16212999 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8347148\charrsid6645626 They all sat together, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8137580 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8347148\charrsid6645626 Did you always have the same places at the table?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16212999 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8347148\charrsid6645626 We did.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8137580 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8347148\charrsid6645626 How was the meal served, by whom?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16212999 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8347148\charrsid6645626 By mother.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8137580 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8347148\charrsid6645626 How did she serve it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16212999 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8347148\charrsid6645626 She put the biggest portions for the eldest, and it came down to the smallest for the littlest.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8137580 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8347148\charrsid6645626 So she put it all out on plates?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16212999 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8347148\charrsid6645626 That's right. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8137580 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8347148\charrsid6645626 What order were you served in?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16212999 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8347148\charrsid6645626 It were always - they always started - with - they put dad's out, and then all the children, and mother always came last, she always -

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8137580 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8347148\charrsid6645626 Did they serve the little ones first or the eldest first?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16212999 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8347148\charrsid6645626 The eldest first, they always went down - and that to the youngest.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8137580 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8347148\charrsid6645626 Where did the younger brother and sisters sit before they could feed themselves?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16212999 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8347148\charrsid6645626 Where - where did they sit?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8137580 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8347148\charrsid6645626 You were next to youngest weren't you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16212999 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8347148\charrsid6645626 Mm.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8137580 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8347148\charrsid6645626 Do you remember where your little brother used to sit before he could feed himself?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16212999 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8347148\charrsid6645626 
The - moth - mother used - father used to sit head of the table, and - the eldest girl was always next to him, then the next and the next and the next and - the youngest, and we all went round, you know, as - in ages.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8137580 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8347148\charrsid6645626 When your little brother was too small to feed himself properly do you remember where he sat, did he have a high chair?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16212999 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8347148\charrsid6645626 He - he used to sit on his mother knee and they used to hand feed 'em in them days.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8137580 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8347148\charrsid6645626 Your mother used to feed him?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16212999 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8347148\charrsid6645626 Mm.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8137580 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8347148\charrsid6645626 Did your father ever do it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16212999 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8347148\charrsid6645626 Oh many a time you know, if she - if she were pushed you know, father'd do it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8137580 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8347148\charrsid6645626 He'd have him on his knee?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16212999 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8347148\charrsid6645626 Mm.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8137580 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8347148\charrsid6645626 Can you tell me, was your mother an easy person to talk to?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16212999 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8347148\charrsid6645626 She were - 
she were very easy to talk to because - with having this shop she'd to - be friendly with everybody you know and - oh she - a cheerful person and - it radiated through the family you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8137580 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8347148\charrsid6645626 You all found her easy to talk to?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16212999 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8347148\charrsid6645626 That's right. You could take your troubles to 'em and -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8137580 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8347148\charrsid6645626 Did she show affection?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16212999 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8347148\charrsid6645626 She did. To - and - and - and she didn't make one of - flesh of one and fish of another, they're all alike. Mm.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8137580 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8347148\charrsid6645626 She was very motherly was she?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16212999 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8347148\charrsid6645626 Very motherly, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8137580 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8347148\charrsid6645626 And she was very affectionate?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16212999 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8347148\charrsid6645626 Very affectionate.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8137580 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8347148\charrsid6645626 You never felt lacking in affection?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16212999 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8347148\charrsid6645626 No, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8137580 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8347148\charrsid6645626 If you had any worries could you share them with her or not?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16212999 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8347148\charrsid6645626 Could you what?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8137580 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8347148\charrsid6645626 Could you share your worries with her or not?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16212999 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8347148\charrsid6645626 Oh ye
s, yes, you - you - you - you told your mum and - and - and if it - if it were too big for her dad used to take it up as well and - they'd - give you their advice and pat you on the head and that were it you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8137580 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8347148\charrsid6645626 Was your father an easy person to talk to?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16212999 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8347148\charrsid6645626 
Oh yes, he were very well - he - he - very freely spoken, and - and he'd help anybody, it didn't matter - if he - he knew anybody were ill he'd - kill - kill a couple of pigeons for 'em or - anybody wanted it they always -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8137580 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8347148\charrsid6645626 You kept pigeons as well did you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16212999 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8347148\charrsid6645626 Oh yes, kept pigeons.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8137580 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8347148\charrsid6645626 You had quite a lot of livestock?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16212999 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8347148\charrsid6645626 Mm.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8137580 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8347148\charrsid6645626 You kept pigeons and pigs?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16212999 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8347148\charrsid6645626 Mm. But they're all things that you could - implement in the family you know Mm.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8137580 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8347148\charrsid6645626 Did you sell pigeon pie when you were at the shop?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16212999 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8347148\charrsid6645626 Yes, we used to have pigeon pies.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8137580 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8347148\charrsid6645626 Was your father a man who showed affection?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16212999 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8347148\charrsid6645626 
He - my - he was a - a loving father was ours. They were strict - strict in the home, but - he showed a lot of affection for us. He - he - he'd take us miles you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8137580 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8347148\charrsid6645626 For walks and things?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16212999 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8347148\charrsid6645626 Mm.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8137580 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8347148\charrsid6645626 If you had any worries could you share them with him?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16212999 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8347148\charrsid6645626 Oh yes, you could always tell your dad. He - and he used to notice if you were worried. Now then lad, what's troubling you? You'd te
ll him. And he'd put his hand on your shoulder and - he'd talk to you and - and - this don't happen nowadays you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8137580 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8347148\charrsid6645626 How did your parents expect you to behave towards them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16212999 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8347148\charrsid6645626 Well - I never heard anybody give - give any cheek to - to my parents,
 well they daren't. They were strict. And - and he would go to Sunday school at - at - at Sunday night with you you know. But we had to go to Sunday school twice at - you know, at Sunday and - we daren't miss. I mean - it were - it were only a little Sund
a
y school then you know and - everybody knew everybody else. And I always remember me father, he always - they - they could ask for hymns they wanted, you know, and - he used to - always ask for the same thing, the Rugged Cross, and while they were singing
 it - tears used to run down his cheeks. Mm.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8137580 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8347148\charrsid6645626 So your parents expected you to behave with a degree of respect towards them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16212999 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8347148\charrsid6645626 That's right. Mm. And he - he used to have all - he used to have all of us - we - we all used to be in the Sunday school co
ncerts you know. And - we used to come home and say, well, what are you doing, what are you doing and - why aren't you - why haven't you got some - well I can't sing right. Ah well you'll learn the recitation then.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8137580 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8347148\charrsid6645626 He encouraged you take part in this type of thing?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16212999 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8347148\charrsid6645626 Yes, that's right.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8137580 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8347148\charrsid6645626 Did your parents bring you up to behave towards your brothers and sisters in a certain way?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16212999 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8347148\charrsid6645626 We'd always had - had to help one another, if they were in any kind of trouble, you know, as kiddies used to fig
ht - the eldest used to come and - straighten it all out you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8137580 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8347148\charrsid6645626 I think you were saying that you'd all to help each other?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16212999 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8347148\charrsid6645626 Yes. And it was al - I was always detailed to look after me younger brother. And the sisters, the eldest - looked after
 the next and - so and so down, but when it came to the lads, I were responsible for me brother.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8137580 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8347148\charrsid6645626 Did they say you should hit back or not if another child hurt you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16212999 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8347148\charrsid6645626 Me father always said, look, stick up for yourselves. And you had to do.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8137580 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9137040\charrsid6645626 And he didn't m}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8347148\charrsid6645626 ind at all if you did hit back?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16212999 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8347148\charrsid6645626 Had to.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8137580 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8347148\charrsid6645626 What kind of people do you think your parents hoped you would grow up to be?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16212999 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8347148\charrsid6645626 Well me father al - he always said, if you - if you can't do owt - if you can't do owt good - never do nowt bad.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8137580 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8347148\charrsid6645626 Can you remember anything else that they used to say to you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16212999 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8347148\charrsid6645626 Pardon?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8137580 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8347148\charrsid6645626 Do you remember anything else they used to say to you, your mother and father? Did you remember them discussing the future of the children?

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16212999 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8347148\charrsid6645626 Well - when - when - w
hen - when you were going - when - me father said - he used to say, now then - it's time that started working, the starts working next week, and - now then - what spending money we going to give him? And it'd be tuppence a week you see or something like t
hat, a lot of money in them days you know, but you see I - I used to do these paper rounds and - I had this one and nine I got give it to me father and he used to give me three}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9137040\charrsid6645626  }{\rtlch\fcs1 
\af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8347148\charrsid6645626 pence. But I used to share it with me brother. And if we spent any money we had to spend it in the little shop we had. So it came back in.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8137580 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8347148\charrsid6645626 Did your parents bring you up to consider certain things important in life?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16212999 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8347148\charrsid6645626 No - always show respect for older people. And don't be cheeky because if you're cheeky it'll come back to me 
and you know what you'll get. And we got it.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8137580 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8347148\charrsid6645626 Do you remember what they thought of swearing?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16212999 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8347148\charrsid6645626 Pardon?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8137580 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8347148\charrsid6645626 Do you remember what they thought of swearing? Anyone swearing.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16212999 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8347148\charrsid6645626 My father never swore. Never swore in the home. He might have done at work but - he never swore in the home.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8137580 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8347148\charrsid6645626 What did he think of anyone else who did?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16212999 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8347148\charrsid6645626 He - he took a dim view of it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8137580 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8347148\charrsid6645626 When grown ups were talking were you allowed to join in?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16212999 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9137040\charrsid6645626 Yes. But - not if there }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8347148\charrsid6645626 are visitors in. Mm.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8137580 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8347148\charrsid6645626 If you did something that your parents disapproved of, that they were cross about, what would happen?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16212999 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8347148\charrsid6645626 Well - father used to get his belt out. Yes. Yes, and - he - you knew you had done it, and you didn't do it again.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8137580 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8347148\charrsid6645626 Was there anything else you used to get if they were cross with you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16212999 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8347148\charrsid6645626 No, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8137580 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8347148\charrsid6645626 What about your mother, what would she do if she was cross?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16212999 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8347148\charrsid6645626 
She - mother were very passive you see, she used to tell dad - what had happened. She shielded us a lot but - she couldn't shield us everything.
 But - she never laid her hand on us, I can never remember mother - laying her hand on us at all. If - if there - anybody had to be punished - any punishment - it was me dad.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8137580 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8347148\charrsid6645626 How often would it happen that you'd get slapped in this way?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16212999 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8347148\charrsid6645626 Very rarely, very rarely.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8137580 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8347148\charrsid6645626 Do you remember any particular occasion when you were punished like this?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16212999 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8347148\charrsid6645626 
I was - I was punished for something I never did. I'd an un - we'd an uncle living with us and - he had a tool box under the bed, and my brother must hav
e opened it, and - there were some tools - went, and me father said - has the done it Billy? I said, no. And he said, well our Joe says you have, and he belted me, well - and - he says, you will cry, I will make - and I wouldn't, because I hadn't done it.
 And three weeks after me younger brother told him that - that he'd done it and he did - me father put his hand on me shoulder, he said, now then, he said, forget that hiding lad. And that were it. But -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8137580 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8347148\charrsid6645626 Do you remember how you felt about it after being punished?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16212999 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8347148\charrsid6645626 Well, I was always had that resentment against me younger brother, because he did lace into me did me dad, the belt buckle you know.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8137580 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8347148\charrsid6645626 You just said that you had an uncle staying with you at that time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16212999 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8347148\charrsid6645626 Ah - ah w}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9137040\charrsid6645626 ell, he - he was - he was an app}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid8347148\charrsid6645626 r}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9137040\charrsid6645626 e}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8347148\charrsid6645626 
ntice that - his mother had died and the only - and - and he lived with us until he got married. Just a few months but - mm. Me father wouldn't turn anybody away. Mm.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8137580 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8347148\charrsid6645626 Would you say that you received the ideas you had about how to behav
e from both your parents, or did one play a more important part than the other?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16212999 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8347148\charrsid6645626 Will you repeat that missus?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8137580 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8347148\charrsid6645626 Would you say that you received the ideas you had about how to behave from both your parents, or did one play a more important part than
 the other?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16212999 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8347148\charrsid6645626 
Well - mother - mother used to talk to us quietly. But father didn't. He - he wanted to get down and get the thing straightened out. He didn't want to work all day and then come home and have to straighten a lot of troubles out you know, 
and he got through 'em as quick as he could you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8137580 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8347148\charrsid6645626 When you had a birthday would it be different from any other day?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16212999 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8347148\charrsid6645626 Yes. When we had a birthday we always had a cake, and - I don't know where where he got the ket - got the candles from but we
 always - right - right through - always remember, there were always a birthday - party, and - any of the kiddies that were friendly used to get to come in you know. Mm.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8137580 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8347148\charrsid6645626 So you'd have a cake, did you receive any presents?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16212999 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8347148\charrsid6645626 Yes, well - yes, you might get apple and a orange or - or something like that, bit - yes, nothing elaborate because -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8137580 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8347148\charrsid6645626 And your mother always made a cake with candles?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16212999 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8347148\charrsid6645626 That's right.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8137580 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8347148\charrsid6645626 And you always had a few friends round?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16212999 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8347148\charrsid6645626 That's right.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8137580 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8347148\charrsid6645626 At teatime would it be?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16212999 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8347148\charrsid6645626 That's right.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8137580 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8347148\charrsid6645626 How many friends would you have round do you remember?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16212999 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8347148\charrsid6645626 
Well we used to have - you each had your own mate. I used to bring mine and me - me younger brother, they all brought their own - own friends, all different ages 
but they all came and - they all mucked in and - and - just kiddies all sat round, there were no - no grown ups you know. And then you had - then you had to have a concert, everybody had to sing or recite or something you know and -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8137580 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8347148\charrsid6645626 So if it was say your birthday every child got to bring a friend?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16212999 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8347148\charrsid6645626 That's right.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8137580 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8347148\charrsid6645626 So whoever's birthday it was everybody got to bring a friend?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16212999 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8347148\charrsid6645626 That's right. Mm. There wasn't flesh of one and fish of another, all alike you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8137580 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8347148\charrsid6645626 Did you ever get return visits to peoples houses?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16212999 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8347148\charrsid6645626 
Oh yes. Yes, we used to get invited out to other kiddies you know, when they had 'em. They were a little community on their own up there you know Everybody knew everybody else and -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8137580 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8347148\charrsid6645626 Can you remember anything you did with your mother or father together on Christmas Day?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16212999 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8347148\charrsid6645626 Can I remember what?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8137580 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8347148\charrsid6645626 
Doing anything on Christmas Day? Your mother and father and you and the family, do you remember doing anything all together on Christmas Day?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16212999 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8347148\charrsid6645626 Al - always together. And it - it used to be - but we always had to go to Sunday school twice you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8137580 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8347148\charrsid6645626 On Christmas Day as well?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16212999 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8347148\charrsid6645626 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8137580 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8347148\charrsid6645626 Can you remember playing any games or anything on Christmas Day?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16212999 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8347148\charrsid6645626 No, we weren't allowed to - you weren't allowed - Sunday - 
these games were barred. You'd to go for - you could go for a walk or - or something after tea or something like that but - there - there were no games played on Sunday.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8137580 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8347148\charrsid6645626 But on Christmas Day, what would you do all together then, do you remember?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16212999 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8347148\charrsid6645626 
Well we used to sing carols and - yes. Oh yes, used to - a right get together with the family you know. And anybody that came in they joined in with it you know. In - in those days people used to walk in one another houses you know and - they were friendl
y. And if anyone were ill - say a woman had had a child, well there's no - places - there were no St Johns or anything like that, well - there's always a woman would go in and look after her and - and that or the rest of the neighbours'd all muck in and -
 
and look after the kiddies, see that they got meals, and - they'd make a meal for the fellow when he came home at night, but you know they were only in bed two or three days in them days. But the neighbours - well they were lovely. You - you - you - you k
now it - you notice it now, the - the - the same thing isn't - as it was then. They all had to help one another you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8137580 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8347148\charrsid6645626 Did you have any musical instruments in the home?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16212999 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8347148\charrsid6645626 We had a little organ. And - my eldest - my eldest sister, she learnt to p
lay the organ. And - only a foot-peddle organ you know and all that, and - we used to have sing-songs, hymns and all sorts of - it - well a good old thing, some good old times.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8137580 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8347148\charrsid6645626 So there was just your elder sister played?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16212999 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8347148\charrsid6645626 Mm.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8137580 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8347148\charrsid6645626 You didn't have any other instruments?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16212999 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8347148\charrsid6645626 No, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8137580 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8347148\charrsid6645626 Was there anyone in the family who sang?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16212999 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8347148\charrsid6645626 
Yes, I - yes, I'd two - I'd - I'd a second sister that she was - quite a nice singer. And - well unless she sang the - the - the job wasn't - it wasn't on you know. That's right.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8137580 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8347148\charrsid6645626 Did you ever make music together as a family, you obviously did?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16212999 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8347148\charrsid6645626 Yes, all - yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8137580 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8347148\charrsid6645626 With your eldest sister on the organ?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16212999 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8347148\charrsid6645626 Mm.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8137580 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8347148\charrsid6645626 Did your parents play any games with you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16212999 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8347148\charrsid6645626 Dad always played with us but mother was alw
ays busy. You know, always finding something to do but - dad's always - always play with us. And it didn't matter what you asked him - he'd answer you in some way you know. He wouldn't - he - he never avoid - whatever you - whatever you asked him you know
, he - ask him straight out, and if it were a bit tricky he'd just take you on one side and he'd tell you.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8137580 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8347148\charrsid6645626 Do you remember any particular games you played with him?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16212999 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8347148\charrsid6645626 Well - in them days there were only ludo and - snakes and ladders and all that you know. Excitement you know when you come down a ladder.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8137580 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8347148\charrsid6645626 You never had dominoes or cards or anything like that in the house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16212999 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8347148\charrsid6645626 No, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8137580 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8347148\charrsid6645626 Did you ever play any games outside with him such as football or cricket?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16212999 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8347148\charrsid6645626 Oh at - fa - father, he use
d to - he used to stand on what we call the touch line when they were playing football and - he'd give 'em advice and - yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8137580 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8347148\charrsid6645626 Were there books in the house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16212999 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8347148\charrsid6645626 Yes. Yes, we - we used to have - we'd all have prizes that you got for Sunday school you 
know. And - the elder ones used to learn the younger ones to read you know. And it were a great day when we were all made up with the rubber collars on to go for your prizes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8137580 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8347148\charrsid6645626 Were most of the books in the house children}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087028\charrsid6645626 \rquote }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8347148\charrsid6645626 s books? Or did your mother and father have books as well?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16212999 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8347148\charrsid6645626 
Father and mother didn't do a lot of reading. But - they - they - the used to read a passage of the Bible every night before we went to bed.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8137580 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8347148\charrsid6645626 So you had a Bible?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16212999 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8347148\charrsid6645626 Mm.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8137580 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8347148\charrsid6645626 And mainly children}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087028\charrsid6645626 \rquote }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid8347148\charrsid6645626 s books?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16212999 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8347148\charrsid6645626 Mm.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8137580 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8347148\charrsid6645626 Do you remember your mother or father having any books of their own, other than the Bible?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16212999 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8347148\charrsid6645626 No - no, no, very very few, no. They never had time to read a lot you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8137580 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8347148\charrsid6645626 How about newspapers, did you used to get a newspaper?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16212999 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8347148\charrsid6645626 No. Just one.
 Two, we used to get the Keighley News - and I think it were the News of the World. That was only two papers, and we weren't to look at - allowed to look at the News of the World until you were fifteen year old.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8137580 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8347148\charrsid6645626 So you got the Keighley News which was a weekly?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16212999 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8347148\charrsid6645626 Mm.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8137580 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8347148\charrsid6645626 And that came out on a Saturday?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16212999 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8347148\charrsid6645626 Mm. And on the Sunday this - Sunday paper.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8137580 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8347148\charrsid6645626 You didn't get a daily paper?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16212999 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8347148\charrsid6645626 No. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8137580 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8347148\charrsid6645626 Do you remember your mother or father reading?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16212999 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8347148\charrsid6645626 No. I - I - I - I can remember dad, he used - he used to read the Bible but}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087028\charrsid6645626 
 }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8347148\charrsid6645626 
he had - he were always picking something out of you to go to bed on. And - and he always give you this passage and talked about it and - and then you all - you all knelt down round your mother's knee, everybody, and you said your prayers.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8137580 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8347148\charrsid6645626 Do you remember him reading anything else to you other than the Bible?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16212999 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8347148\charrsid6645626 No. Only when we had these - these prizes that we got from Sunday school and - the children}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid4087028\charrsid6645626 \rquote }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8347148\charrsid6645626 s stories and all that, the eldest used to read out to us you know.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8137580 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8347148\charrsid6645626 The eldest girl would read to the little ones?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16212999 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8347148\charrsid6645626 Mm.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8137580 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8347148\charrsid6645626 Do you remember a funeral in the family before 1919?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16212999 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8347148\charrsid6645626 In the family yes. I had two sisters buried in one day. One - they got this thesis - one was eighteen and the other twenty-on
e and - the other twenty-four. One died at the morning. And - I had to walk practically to Laycock, to - to see the gravedigger - while father were doing other business in the town you know, about the funeral, and when I got back at night - the other sist
e
r had died, and I set off again and told him to make it a double grave. And they buried 'em both in one grave. And - and - and three years after the other sister died. And I can always remember - dad - saying to me, we were going down - he - he'd been to 
m
ake arrangement for the funeral and he had to go to his work on the - on the second day, and as we're going - as we're going down the yard, old Prince Smith - he worked, he'd heard about it, he knocked on the window and he called him in. He said, now then
 Johnnie, he said, I'm sorry to hear about your - your fatality - two in one day, he said, it's heartbreaking lad. How are you for brass? He says, well - I - I've had 'em insured, he said, we'll be all right. He says, well tha}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087028\charrsid6645626 t}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8347148\charrsid6645626 's going to take twenty pound, he sayd, and that'll - tha can pay it back as and when tha}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid4087028\charrsid6645626 t}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8347148\charrsid6645626 
's ready. First week em father went in, after the funeral, and he took five shilling. And he - he took this five shilling to - to this here Prince and he said, now how are you going on, are - are 
you managing all right? He said, well we've got to manage, we've got to live on with them that's living. Now - and he went in second week, and he paid his five shilling again, and he said, you - you're paying too much out. He said, no, he said, as - as lo
ng as I can manage five bob a week he said I'll straighten it up. He went in the third week, and he says, hey, tha}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087028\charrsid6645626 t}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8347148\charrsid6645626 
's caused a right disturbance here. He says, I've lost - I - I can't find book, he sa}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087028\charrsid6645626 y}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8347148\charrsid6645626 
s, secret - my secretary she can't find it neither. He s
aid - I - I'll let tha know when we find it. And me father, he saved up for about six weeks and he - he got to go see old Prince again, he said - we'll forget it lad. And - and he - and he got it for nothing you know. I mean they were - they were good old
 masters in them days you know. And when - when that old fellow died you know they whole works closed down and every - and everybody - everybody at the}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087028\charrsid6645626  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid8347148\charrsid6645626 works lined the funeral route right from - Greenhead Lane you know right down to the - cemetery, everybody - and they got paid for that day.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8137580 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8347148\charrsid6645626 Did this happen before your mother died?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16212999 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8347148\charrsid6645626 This happened when?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8137580 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8347148\charrsid6645626 Before your mother died, the girls died before you mother died?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16212999 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8347148\charrsid6645626 No. They - they - these - my mother had died twelve month before the fir
st one died. And - then - the - these two died and then - the third one died, but she were married. And - then father got married again.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8137580 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8347148\charrsid6645626 I wonder if you can remember a funeral, either your mother's or the one of your sisters, they died before 1919 didn't they?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16212999 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8347148\charrsid6645626 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8137580 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8347148\charrsid6645626 I wonder if you can remember quite clearly and explain to me what happened at the funeral of either your mother or of your two sisters?

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16212999 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8347148\charrsid6645626 Well, I can - I can always - I can remember when the - when they buried me mother. She w
as a big woman, she suffered from Dropsey. And - the - and the coffin were that big - in the room that they couldn't get it out. And they had to - get the front window out, that were in Fell Lane. I can always remember that. But - when they buried me two 
sisters - it were a - a terribly bad winter. And they had to come right down - from Fell Lane - up the town, up West Lane and right through - right through to Laycock, and - two hearses, and about four cabs you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8137580 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8347148\charrsid6645626 So they'd to be buried at Laycock?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16212999 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8347148\charrsid6645626 Mm.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8137580 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8347148\charrsid6645626 What sort of a funeral was it, was it a family affair, who attended?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16212999 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8347148\charrsid6645626 
Who - it were just - everyone - all - all - all your neighbours round and relations from - from where we had 'em. And - in them days used to have a - a funeral tea, a
nd it was always in the chapel - adjoining the church up - up at Laycock, and there-was always a - two kinds of meat, what they always called two kinds of meat, and there was a - and there was a feed put on for the cabbies as well. And -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8137580 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8347148\charrsid6645626 So how many people would you say went up to the cemetery?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16212999 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8347148\charrsid6645626 Pardon?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8137580 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8347148\charrsid6645626 How many people would you say went up to the cemetery,
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16212999 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8347148\charrsid6645626 I reckon - oh sixty to seventy.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8137580 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8347148\charrsid6645626 And they all went in carriages?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16212999 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8347148\charrsid6645626 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8137580 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8347148\charrsid6645626 Would your father have to pay for all these carriages?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16212999 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8347148\charrsid6645626 
No, we - we only had four, but the rest - were up there at - or walked it you know. And - and it were bad weather but - I mean it - it's a thing that's - two in one day, it's a lot isn't it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8137580 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8347148\charrsid6645626 Did everyone have mourning clothes?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16212999 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8347148\charrsid6645626 Oh yes, everybody went in black then. Everybody.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8137580 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8347148\charrsid6645626 Were you taken out visiting neighbours, friends or relations? While you were still at school. Do you remember being taken out visiting?

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16212999 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8347148\charrsid6645626 Biggest part of our relations lived in Fell Lane.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8137580 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8347148\charrsid6645626 Do you remember your parents taking you to actually visit them at their houses?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16212999 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8347148\charrsid6645626 
Oh yes - yes, some - if - if - if they - if there were a wedding of - of any relations, we all had to put your best on and you're all invited and there's always a do for the kiddies you know and -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8137580 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8347148\charrsid6645626 At the house would it be?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16212999 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8347148\charrsid6645626 Mm. Mm. Oh no, they - the - they hadn't halls to go to then you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8137580 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8347148\charrsid6645626 They'd have it in the house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16212999 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8347148\charrsid6645626 That's right. Mm.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8137580 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8347148\charrsid6645626 Other than weddings and things do you remember going to peoples ho
uses, such as friends or relations or neighbours, do you remember visiting them at their houses?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16212999 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8347148\charrsid6645626 
Oh, we - we - we had us own - own little friends you know, that - you could go in their house and they could come in ours - just when they wanted I mean it weren't visiting it were just calling.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8137580 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8347148\charrsid6645626 But you don't remember particularly your parents taking you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16212999 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8347148\charrsid6645626 No, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8137580 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8347148\charrsid6645626 To make a proper visit to anyone?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16212999 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8347148\charrsid6645626 No, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8137580 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8347148\charrsid6645626 Were you ever taken shopping with your parents?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16212999 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8347148\charrsid6645626 Oh - I used to go wit
h me dad every Saturday. Dad used to do all the shopping and - and - of course I - as I told you with this donkey and cart we used to get every - thing - loaded up, for the house and for the shop and -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8137580 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8347148\charrsid6645626 So you always went with your father and the donkey and cart?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16212999 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8347148\charrsid6645626 
Mm. And when I - incidentally when I were five year old and this - this donkey cast its first shoe - dad says, now then, we'll pin this up lad. And - on the outside door - or - in - at 228 Fell Lane - on the coal house door, I - he held m
e on his shoulders while I nailed it up. He said, now that'll be there as long as I lives Willy. When it comes down tha'll die. Well my grandchildren, many a time they've come over - they always pull up in the car to see if the donkey shoe's still there, 
and it's still there in Fell Lane.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8137580 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8347148\charrsid6645626 
Did you ever go out with just your father? You've just told me that you used to go down every Saturday to do the shopping with him, do you remember any other outings that you went on with just your father?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16212999 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8347148\charrsid6645626 Well,
 if me dad were buying - buying a - a - a pig or anything like that - Billy always had to go with him. And we once set off on Sunday morning, and went up to the Herders, that's a - boozer right - right - out at what's called the Herders and - yes, the Her
d
ers, the Herders, and when we got there there were - it were a little old place then, all whitewashed you know, and - when we went in the - they were - they - the old lady, I thought it were the farmer's wife, and she - and he said, I've come about them p
i
gs. Ah well, she says - he's down yonder, you - you'll see him. You can tell which is him, he has a cap on. And - and - yes, so any road went down and - they - they bartered about these pigs and - they were - there were eight, there were nine, but there w
ere eight of 'em - were good pigs and the other one a }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087028\charrsid6645626 waffle}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8347148\charrsid6645626 
 you know. And - - they used to call it reckling in them days. Anyway they bartered these pigs and I think that - me father got 'em for seven bob a piece. Then - they said well - now then he says, 
I'll pay the - he says, no, tha'd better give it to her, she's boss. Anyway we went up to the boozer and - me father got a pint and he says, does thou take sailors? She says, aye, there's some cheese and - cheese and bread there and some onions. And - wel
l
 - get lad a - glass of lemonade, make him a sandwich you know. And - he paid for these pigs, and - he says - them's grand pickles. She said they are. He says, how much is them? Oh, she says, they're for nowt. So he took his red handkerchief out of his po
cket and he put basin in, he says, well this is luck for job, and - and I carried the smallest pig under me arm and this - and this basin of pickles}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087028\charrsid6645626  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid8347148\charrsid6645626 in red handkerchief down home, we drove 'em right from the Herders right down to Fell Lane.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8137580 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8347148\charrsid6645626 They ran in front of you did they?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16212999 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8347148\charrsid6645626 Pardon?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8137580 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8347148\charrsid6645626 You drove them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16212999 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8347148\charrsid6645626 We drove them, yes, yes, we drove them down. Aye.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8137580 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8347148\charrsid6645626 So that would be about five miles wouldn't it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16212999 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8347148\charrsid6645626 Pardon?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8137580 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8347148\charrsid6645626 Would it be about five miles?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16212999 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8347148\charrsid6645626 It's about five miles, yes, they were leg weary when they got home.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8137580 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8347148\charrsid6645626 So you didn't use your donkey and cart for things like that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16212999 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8347148\charrsid6645626 No, no, no, we drove 'em down, mm.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8137580 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8347148\charrsid6645626 Did the people who had the Herders have the farm as well?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16212999 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8347148\charrsid6645626 They - it had - it were a farm as well as a b
oozer - as the Herders. And it - it were called Herders because - the sheep herders used to use it you know. And they always called Therders, I don't know why.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8137580 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8347148\charrsid6645626 Do you remember any other outings with your parents, on Bank Holidays, perhaps Easter Monday, Whit Monday, things like that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16212999 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8347148\charrsid6645626 
Well - we used to set off to Ilkley. We used to take - we used to take us all over Ilkley, a long walk, we always had a ball and a - a stick a piece and - braying 'em up the road you know, and when you got there you'
d taken your own food but you used to buy the tea you know. And - then you'd come home leg weary, well - there are those days to remember you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8137580 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8347148\charrsid6645626 Was it nearly always to Ilkley?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16212999 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8347148\charrsid6645626 That's right.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8137580 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8347148\charrsid6645626 Did you ever go anywhere else on a Bank Holiday do you remember?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16212999 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8347148\charrsid6645626 No, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8137580 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8347148\charrsid6645626 You said you used to go to Morecambe, was that not at Bank Holidays you used to go?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16212999 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8347148\charrsid6645626 No, this - this were in summer when - when they ran these cheap trips you know.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8137580 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8347148\charrsid6645626 Did your mother used to go over to Ilkley as well?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16212999 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8347148\charrsid6645626 Mother - you see, with having the shop - someone had to stay there. But father used to take all us kiddies and - away we'd go.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8137580 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8347148\charrsid6645626 But when you went to Ilkley on Bank Holidays did she used to close the shop up and go with you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16212999 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8347148\charrsid6645626 No - no - she used to keep the shop open you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8137580 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8347148\charrsid6645626 Even on a Bank Holiday she'd keep it open?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16212999 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8347148\charrsid6645626 Mm. See, it was the only shop up there and they couldn't get anything anywhere else. There are not so many now are there.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8137580 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8347148\charrsid6645626 Did you ever go away for a holiday?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16212999 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8347148\charrsid6645626 
Yes, we used to go to Morecambe, we had an aunt that lived in Morecambe, and - in them days - you had to take your food with you. Used to pack 'en in the old tin hat boxes and - the little trunk and - and - you - you fed yourself you see. I mean,
 the stuff were getting a bit stale by the end of the week but - anyway you'd a week. But - we - we - we didn't get much to spend, if you got a donkey ride in them days you were very very lucky you know. Then we could come home and ride us own.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8137580 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8347148\charrsid6645626 You always stayed with this aunt did you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16212999 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8347148\charrsid6645626 Pardon?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8137580 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8347148\charrsid6645626 You always stayed with your aunt?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16212999 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8347148\charrsid6645626 That's right.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8137580 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8347148\charrsid6645626 And you always provided your own food?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16212999 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8347148\charrsid6645626 That's right.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8137580 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8347148\charrsid6645626 You took it with you from home?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16212999 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8347148\charrsid6645626 Mm.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8137580 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8347148\charrsid6645626 How long did you stay for when you used to go there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16212999 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8347148\charrsid6645626 We used to go on Saturday and come - and come back the following Saturday.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8137580 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8347148\charrsid6645626 Was it fairly regularly that you went?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16212999 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8347148\charrsid6645626 We used to go every year. Mm.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8137580 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8347148\charrsid6645626 Is that what they called the Parish Feast Week?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16212999 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8347148\charrsid6645626 Mm. Just at - don't put this on tape.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8137580 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8347148\charrsid6645626 When you stayed with your auntie at Morecambe you used to go every year did you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16212999 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8347148\charrsid6645626 Every year, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8137580 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8347148\charrsid6645626 Did you ever go anywhere different than Morecambe for your holidays?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16212999 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8347148\charrsid6645626 No, I don't think - no, no - we never went any - because the fare were more for - other places you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8137580 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8347148\charrsid6645626 That was the nearest place you could go to?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16212999 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8347148\charrsid6645626 Mm. Or - from - from going on holidays to the next year you'd to save all your pennies, all that you could, it were for your holiday and y
ou looked forward to that week and - and that were it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8137580 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8347148\charrsid6645626 Which members of the family went?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16212999 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8347148\charrsid6645626 The - all of us.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8137580 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8347148\charrsid6645626 All seven of you went?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16212999 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8347148\charrsid6645626 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8137580 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8347148\charrsid6645626 And your mother closed the shop then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16212999 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8347148\charrsid6645626 She - she - she stayed at home. I - not - I can - I
 can only remember mother going on one holiday once and - we had to get someone in to look after the shop.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8137580 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8347148\charrsid6645626 Did she only have that one holiday?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16212999 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8347148\charrsid6645626 Mm.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8137580 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8347148\charrsid6645626 Otherwise she always stayed at home?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16212999 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8347148\charrsid6645626 That's right. She was tied down to the job.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8137580 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8347148\charrsid6645626 When you were at Morecambe I think you said you had donkey rides?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16212999 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8347148\charrsid6645626 Yes.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8137580 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8347148\charrsid6645626 Can you remember doing anything else while you were there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16212999 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8347148\charrsid6645626 Can I remember what?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8137580 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8347148\charrsid6645626 Doing anything else at Morecambe?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16212999 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8347148\charrsid6645626 Oh, build sandcastles and - we would go pad
dling and - days weren't long enough you know, you - you were tired out by six o'clock and you're all in bed by seven.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8137580 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8347148\charrsid6645626 Did you do anything else, can you think of anything else you did together?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16212999 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8347148\charrsid6645626 No, well - you see - go - going to the sea I - it -
 it were an occasion, I mean - there - there were - to - we had to make us own fun and play with anybody else's kiddies you know but everybody seemed happy in them days.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8137580 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8347148\charrsid6645626 How long did you do this for?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16212999 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8347148\charrsid6645626 Well right - right - right up to the girls - 
the - being four - fourteen. We - we went - we went years, until the girls were - eldest were fourteen, and then it just seemed to drop off you know after that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8137580 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8347148\charrsid6645626 Didn't you have any annual holidays then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16212999 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8347148\charrsid6645626 No, not after that, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8137580 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8347148\charrsid6645626 Could, you te
ll me how you spent Saturdays in those days? This is the time when you were still at school, when you finished school what did you do on a Saturday?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16212999 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8347148\charrsid6645626 Well, I - personally I had always plenty to do, I had those - either pig - pig huts to clean out, the
 donkey to groom - get it ready for Saturday dinner - every day, every Saturday that were my job to meet me father in the town with this you know, and - this cart were made out - out of an handcart and it - it extended it so we could get all sorts on you 
know. And - and then if there were any little gala or anything round about - Sunday school gala, we had a saddle and the kids used to pay - ha'penny a piece to have a ride, and it went to the church funds you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8137580 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8347148\charrsid6645626 Did you used to take the donkey?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16212999 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8347148\charrsid6645626 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8137580 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8347148\charrsid6645626 You and your father?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16212999 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8347148\charrsid6645626 Yes. Mm.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8137580 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8347148\charrsid6645626 How about Sundays, you've already told me that you used to go to Sunday school? Did you go twice a day to Sunday school?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16212999 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8347148\charrsid6645626 We - we always went - on the Sunday morning - and - and on the evening service, used to start at six o'clock.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8137580 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8347148\charrsid6645626 So you went to Sunday school and church?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16212999 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8347148\charrsid6645626 That's right.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8137580 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8347148\charrsid6645626 You had different clothes for Sunday, you always had best things to put on?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16212999 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8347148\charrsid6645626 That's right.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8137580 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8347148\charrsid6645626 Did you ever play games on a Sunday?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16212999 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8347148\charrsid6645626 Yes - he - he wouldn't let you play outside. You had your best clothes on. You had to organise 'em in - in - in - in your home you know.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8137580 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8347148\charrsid6645626 Did your parents think it wrong to work or play on a Sunday?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16212999 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8347148\charrsid6645626 Well - me - me father used to try and keep the Sabbat
h, as the Sabbath. And - we always finished up at night with this organ at Sunday you know, and everybody singing, and then they had to do an individual turn you know, you - and you'd always got to tell your dad - what you'd learnt at Sunday school, and w
hat you'd been talking about you know and - and that. Well -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8137580 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8347148\charrsid6645626 Did your parents go to church?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16212999 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8347148\charrsid6645626 
Father - father went every Sunday night. But mother didn't, only on special occasions, anniversaries and - cantatas, what they - used to call cantatas.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8137580 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8347148\charrsid6645626 What were they?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16212999 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8347148\charrsid6645626 Well - where they all get dressed up and - gave - they gave little plays and then -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8137580 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8347148\charrsid6645626 A sort of concert was it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16212999 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8347148\charrsid6645626 That's right.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8137580 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8347148\charrsid6645626 What was the denomination of the church that you all attended?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16212999 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8347148\charrsid6645626 Wesleyan Methodist.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8137580 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8347148\charrsid6645626 How often did your father go?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16212999 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8347148\charrsid6645626 Father went every Sunday night.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8137580 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8347148\charrsid6645626 And you went every Sunday night?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16212999 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8347148\charrsid6645626 Every - had to do - we all went - all of the children.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8137580 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8347148\charrsid6645626 All of the children went?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16212999 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8347148\charrsid6645626 Pardon?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8137580 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8347148\charrsid6645626 All the children went?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16212999 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8347148\charrsid6645626 Yes. Unless they were - poorly, but - everybody went.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8137580 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8347148\charrsid6645626 And you went to Sunday school in the morning. Were there any Sunday school outings?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16212999 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8347148\charrsid6645626 Oh well - yes, they used to organize these - trips up to - up - up to Newsholme Dene everybody went. And - then t
hey used to have these - when it were anniversary Sunday they used to - everybody came out the church, all the kiddies and that and sang at - people's houses that were ill and - all go down and - a little prayer you know}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid4087028\charrsid6645626  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8347148\charrsid6645626 at}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087028\charrsid6645626  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8347148\charrsid6645626 
side and then - sing for these people.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8137580 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8347148\charrsid6645626 So how often would you go to Newsholme Dene, just once during the summer would it be?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16212999 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8347148\charrsid6645626 No, we used to - we used to set off - in - in fine weather - he'd say, we're all off to Newsholme Dene, and away we'd go.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8137580 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8347148\charrsid6645626 Did you walk?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16212999 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8347148\charrsid6645626 Oh yes, you - all had to walk, there were no transport or anything.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8137580 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8347148\charrsid6645626 What other social activities organized by the chapel did you take part in?
