\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16212999 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8347148\charrsid6645626 Well, through your - your father - he'd say - he - he'd tell you - I - have a lad that's ready f
or start, and where can he start and - and he - and he suggested in the fitting, well when you went there you were all - young apprentices on benches, and you'd to file gro}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14437611\charrsid6645626 ss}{\rtlch\fcs1 
\af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8347148\charrsid6645626  - file nuts up, brass nuts up at three}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14437611\charrsid6645626  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8347148\charrsid6645626 
pence a gross. You could earn - a fiver - 
five - five to - five and six a week. But you were piece work and - all these were counted and weighed out as you done 'em. Now - and then when it come - when it came your turn - you were moved into a batch to work with about three men and - and two more 
apprentices, and then you - you were on piecework building these machines. Well the harder you worked the more coppers you got. It wasn't shillings, it were coppers.
