\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8137580 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8347148\charrsid6645626 And you got about five and six a week?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16212999 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8347148\charrsid6645626 That's right.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8137580 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8347148\charrsid6645626 Did you feel it was a fair wage?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16212999 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8347148\charrsid6645626 No, because - we always had to seem - work a lot harder than what we - for the money we got you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8137580 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8347148\charrsid6645626 Did you give this money to your mother still?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16212999 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8347148\charrsid6645626 Yes, all - ev - every week.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8137580 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8347148\charrsid6645626 What was that spent on?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16212999 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8347148\charrsid6645626 It went same in the food and -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8137580 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8347148\charrsid6645626 How did you get on with the other people you worked with at Prince Smiths?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16212999 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8347148\charrsid6645626 Oh well, all right.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8137580 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8347148\charrsid6645626 How did your employer treat you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16212999 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8347148\charrsid6645626 Well - I - I can always remember one - one thing - I were walking do
wn the yard one day - and there were a nut lying in the passage, and I kicked it, and somebody said, hey, laddie, and I turned round and it were Prince Smith himself. Old Prin. Come here he says. How long has that worked here? I says, two days. Two days. 
H
e says, what they call that? I said, Billy Barnes. He said, that's your father in - blacksmith shop? I said, yes sir. Or yes - yes sir to him you see. Ah well, he said - now come - who's the gaffer, and took me down the gaffer, he said, now this lad's wor
k
ing for me for - a week, for me, he says, not for ee, he's working for me a week. Come on, and he - he - he took me into the stores, he got a lump of chalk - and he drew a big square. It were six foot square. And - he looked about the yard, he said, now t
h
en, that nut tha kicked - it's there. I had to go all round these works wherever I sees a washer, a screw, a nut or a bolt, put it here. And - and - end of the seven days it were four foot high and I couldn't get any more in, 'cos I'd picked 'em up from a
l
l over. And - then he took me back to me gaffer, and he said, now - this is - this lad's done a good job. But I'm going to give him a lecture, he says, in front of thee. He said, they'd been thine nuts, bolts and washers tha wouldn't have kicked 'em about
.
 He said, 'cos - they cost ha'penny a piece, he says, and look at how many ha'pennies and pennies there is there, he said, I'm going to give thee something now, he said, and always remember this, always treat other people's stuff as - that'd treat thee ow
n, and he give me a - a - half a - half a sovereign, yes. And I took that to me father and - but that was a lesson to me. But he - he - he knew - he'd been to everyone in the works. The old - gaffers in them days you know And - I always respected him.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8137580 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8347148\charrsid6645626 How did you feel about the work at Prince Smith's?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16212999 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8347148\charrsid6645626 Well, you - you - you - it - though - though they were lowly paid - they were happy crowd. They were always - always singing and -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8137580 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8347148\charrsid6645626 You were happy there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16212999 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8347148\charrsid6645626 Yes, quite - yes. Were - were an ha
ppy day when I had to finish, when I had to go in the - Army when I were eighteen, the day I was eighteen. I told you that didn't I, but - I told - I had to go in - in the Army on -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8137580 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8347148\charrsid6645626 You went in the Army in 1918?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16212999 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8347148\charrsid6645626 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8137580 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8347148\charrsid6645626 When you came out of the Army, in 1919 would it be?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16212999 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8347148\charrsid6645626 Mm.
